values:
I actually have been writing. Really. It's almost done, actually. Latley, though, i've been drawing. I'll post some stuff once i figure out how to work my scanner. (evil creature that it is...) 

below is the link to Not so different after all, incase anybody wants to read it. Remember the first couple of chapters suck royally, so please read on, i swear it get better.

http://www.fanfiction.net/secure/live_preview.php?storyid=2194683&chapter=1

And knowing my luck, that link doesn't work. I hate trying to link to fanfiction, it's damn near impossible.

UPDATE: Is it just me or does that link actually work?!? It did for me, but who knows...

I swear I will update Not so different after all. Really. I will. Soon. I'm thinking within a week. I'm sorry for the delay, my muses just haven't been co-operating. I've started about twenty one shots, (most dark, scary and overall depressing), but not actually finished any of them. So guys, thanks for waiting, and don't give up faith just yet! I am alive and writing! I'm thinking within a week. 

Oh, and i'm a beta now! Check out 'Slytherin in Mind' at ff.net.

Hello all.... This is a question for those of you who use livejournal. you know when you post a picture or story, how you do somthing like this:

Story title: 
Chapter Title:
Warnings:
Summary

(catchy phrase that links you to story)


How exactly do you make catchy phrase into usefull link? all help is appreciated.

Hello all. I'm going to be blunt about this: I'm not going to update this journal unless somebody tells me that they're reading it. If not, i'll simply put everything in my A/Ns, i will miss somethings, so if you want to know what's happening with me, tell me you read this. 

Anyways! on my fics... i've TEMPORARILY abandoned not my life, not my problem, but i'll pick it back up when not so different is done. On not so different: Getting closer... my snoggage forecast is for chapter fourteen. 

Yours Truly, 

Hanna Star-Runner

Welcome to the live journal for Hanna Star-Runner! (me) If we haven't been previously introduced, I'm a thirteen year old authoress, my name is Hanna Star-Runner, but call me Hanna, and Since this is the first entry, i'll tell you a bit about myself:

I Love Harry Potter
I Write both Fafcition for ff.net, and poetry for fictionpress.com
Yeah, I'm a Draco/Harry Shipper. It's a hard ship to be in, because it'll never happen in the books.
I play b flat clarinet and the tenor saxaphone, and am second clarinet in my school's band
I pitch for fast pitch softball.

And now, an update on my fics! Well, not so different after all should be updated within a day. Not so sure about not my problem, not my life, but i would guess with in the week. There isn't much else to say, but if you've got questions about anything, shoot me an e-mail at hannastarrunner@yahoo.com

Yours truly,
Hanna Star-Runner
